o%20King%20Harsha%E2%80%99s%20Prayag%2C%20provided%20an%20account%20of%20the%20Kumbh%20Mela.%20Abul%20Fazl%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Ain-i-Akbari%2C%E2%80%99%20written%20in%201590%2C%20also%20details%20the%20Kumbha%20or%20Magha%20Mela%2C%20as%20it%20was%20commonly%20referred%20to%20then.%20Munshi%20Sujan%20Rai%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EKhulasat-ut-Tawarikh%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20written%20in%201695%2C%20chronicles%20multiple%20Kumbh%20Melas%20at%20Haridwar%2C%20Trimbak%20(near%20Nashik%2C%20at%20the%20source%20of%20the%20Godavari%20River)%2C%20and%20Prayag.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20thousands%20of%20years%2C%20crores%20of%20Hindus%20have%20actively%20participated%20in%20the%20Kumbh%20Melas.%20This%20tradition%20did%20not%20halt%20or%20stutter%20even%20during%20the%20years%20of%20Mughal%20rule%20and%20the%20British%20Raj.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fa-lesson-on-temples-from-swami-vivekananda%5C%22%3EA%20Lesson%20on%20Temples%20From%20Swami%20Vivekananda%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERam%20Mandir%20inauguration%2C%20a%20political%20event%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Ram%20Mandir%20campaign%2C%20the%20build%20up%20on%20social%20media%2C%20the%20intertwining%20of%20it%20with%20the%20Modi%20cult%2C%20the%20raucous%20nature%20of%20it%2C%20the%20merchandising%20of%20it%2C%20the%20face-paint%2C%20the%20flags%2C%20the%20roping%20in%20of%20Bollywood%20celebs%20as%20amplifiers%20of%20the%20event%20%E2%80%93%20made%20it%20far%20more%20similar%20to%20a%20jamboree%20like%20the%20Indian%20Premier%20League.%20A%20new%20mandir%20does%20not%20need%20the%20build-up%20that%20comes%20before%20a%20major%20Bollywood%20film.%20So%20why%20were%20we%20subjected%20to%20all%20the%20hype%3F%20Because%2C%20the%20inauguration%20of%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20was%20a%20political%20event.%20It%20was%20the%20culmination%20of%20a%20political%20campaign%20that%20had%20to%20be%20seriously%20played%20up.%20And%20it%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20my%20quick%20uttering%20of%20the%20Gayatri%20Mantra%20at%20home%2C%20my%20visit%20to%20the%20neighbourhood%20mandir%2C%20my%20trip%20to%20Haridwar%20with%20the%20ashes%20of%20my%20grandparent%2C%20even%20mass%20events%20like%20the%20Kumbh%2C%20or%20the%20daily%20churn%20of%20the%20faithful%20that%20we%20see%20on%20the%20ghats%20of%20Varanasi%20%E2%80%93%20all%20these%20are%20deeply%20personal%20spiritual%20acts%20and%20journeys%2C%20for%20all%20practicing%20Hindus.%20It%20does%20not%20require%20hype%20to%20urge%20me%20or%20any%20other%20Hindu%20to%20do%20any%20of%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20also%20examine%20the%20argument%20about%20how%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20will%20%E2%80%98decolonise%E2%80%99%20the%20Hindu%20mind.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20already%20described%20how%20Hindus%20have%20steadily%20practiced%20their%20faith%20over%20the%20centuries%2C%20irrespective%20of%20the%20medieval%20despot%20who%20ran%20their%20lives%20at%20any%20given%20time%2C%20some%20kind%2C%20some%20cruel%2C%20some%20self-serving%2C%20Hindu%2C%20Christian%20and%20Muslim%20alike.%20For%20most%20Hindus%2C%20when%20it%20came%20to%20the%20practice%20of%20their%20religion%2C%20they%20didn%E2%80%99t%20need%20any%20decolonising%20when%20India%20achieved%20independence%20in%201947.%20There%20was%20no%20sense%20of%20%E2%80%98religious%20inferiority%E2%80%99%20to%20shrug%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGandhi%E2%80%99s%20Satyagraha%20%E2%80%98decolonised%E2%80%99%20the%20Indian%20mind%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20was%20needed%20was%20mass%20political%20emancipation%2C%20and%20in%20the%2030%20years%20preceding%201947%2C%20that%20push%20came%20from%20Gandhi.%20His%20unique%20mobilisation%20of%20crores%20of%20Indians%20to%20participate%20in%20non-violent%20protest%20and%20resistance%20made%20each%20of%20them%20a%20stakeholder%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20freedom.%20In%20doing%20so%2C%20he%20facilitated%20a%20mass%20shedding%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20colonial%20mindset.%20Thousands%20of%20freedom%20fighters%20went%20to%20jail%2C%20hundreds%20were%20beaten%20in%20lathi%20charges%2C%20and%20hundreds%20were%20killed%20%E2%80%93%20an%20unprecedented%20number%20of%20Indians%20were%20invested%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20freedom%2C%20and%20they%20remained%20invested%20even%20after%20August%201947.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20my%20mind%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20why%20our%20fledgling%20democracy%20did%20not%20unravel%20like%20that%20of%20many%20countries%20that%20emerged%20from%20colonialism.%20A%20young%20nation%20would%20not%20have%20grown%20from%20strength%20to%20strength%20as%20a%20democracy%20if%20it%20had%20not%20decisively%20broken%20away%20from%20its%20colonial%20past.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20the%20BJP%20wants%20to%20break%20away%20from%20is%20not%20India%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98colonial%E2%80%99%20past%2C%20but%20its%20post-colonial%20%E2%80%98Nehruvian%E2%80%99%20past.%20The%20aversion%20to%20Nehru%2C%20and%20a%20more%20discreet%20aversion%20to%20Gandhi%2C%20is%20present%20simply%20because%20Hindutva%20ideologues%20need%20to%20%E2%80%98clear%20the%20shelf%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20earlier%20icons%20and%20make%20room%20for%20their%20own.%20But%20they%20can%E2%80%99t%20do%20that%20without%20attacking%20them%20and%20their%20contributions%20and%20accusing%20them%20of%20failing%20to%20rid%20India%20of%20its%20%E2%80%98colonial%20mindset.%E2%80%99%20India%20did%20shed%20its%20British%20past%20on%20August%2015%2C%201947%2C%20in%20mind%2C%20spirit%2C%20and%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fayodhyatimeline%5C%22%3EAyodhya%3A%20Once%20There%20Was%20a%20Mosque%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98superpower%E2%80%99%20moment%20came%20before%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20even%20at%20the%20risk%20of%20sounding%20a%20bit%20simplistically%20ra-ra-ish%