d%20work%20on%20my%20health.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20Denver's%20basic%20income%20program%20works%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fubi-cash-payments-reduced-homelessness-increased-employment-denver-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDBIP%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20began%20in%202021%2C%20was%20granted%20%242%20million%20from%20the%20city%20to%20provide%20over%20800%20participants%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faustin-guarunteed-basic-income-gbi-ubi-housing-security-homeless-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecash%20payments%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20help%20them%20get%20back%20on%20their%20feet.%20An%20additional%20%243%20million%20in%20funding%20from%20the%20Colorado%20Trust%20and%20an%20anonymous%20foundation%20will%20give%20participants%20another%20six%20months%20of%20payments%20%E2%80%94%20and%20will%20allow%2039%20more%20residents%20to%20participate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20first%20year%2C%20the%20project%20gave%20participants%20either%20%241%2C000%20monthly%2C%20%24500%20monthly%20with%20%246%2C500%20upfront%2C%20or%20%2450%20each%20month%20as%20a%20control%20group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20groups%20reported%20significant%20improvements%20in%20their%20quality%20of%20life%2C%20researchers%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Denver's%20Center%20for%20Housing%20and%20Homelessness%20Research%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsocialwork.du.edu%2Fchhr%2Fresearch%2Fproject%2Fdenver-basic-income-project%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20included%20financial%20wellness%20and%20safe%20housing%2C%20though%20those%20with%20larger%20payments%20had%20the%20largest%20gains.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20participants%20in%20the%20program%20said%20they%20felt%20more%20stable%2C%20safer%2C%20and%20happier%20after%20receiving%20the%20payments.%20At%20the%20six-month%20mark%2C%20all%20groups%20had%20an%20over%2030%25%20rate%20of%20staying%20in%20a%20home%20or%20apartment%20that%20they%20rent%20or%20own%20%E2%80%94%20this%20was%20at%20or%20below%2010%25%20at%20the%20enrollment%20date.%20The%20percentage%20of%20participants%20experiencing%20homelessness%20greatly%20fell%20%E2%80%94%20and%20dropped%20to%200%25%20for%20those%20receiving%20%241%2C000%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMany%20participants%20reported%20that%20they%20have%20used%20the%20money%20to%20pay%20off%20debt%2C%20repair%20their%20car%2C%20secure%20housing%2C%20and%20enroll%20in%20a%20course%2C%26quot%3B%20Mark%20Donovan%2C%20the%20project's%20founder%20and%20executive%20director%2C%20%3Cu%3Epreviously%20told%20Business%20Insider%3C%2Fu%3E.%20%26quot%3BThese%20are%20all%20paths%20that%20could%20eventually%20lead%20participants%20out%20of%20poverty%20and%20allow%20them%20to%20be%20less%20dependent%20on%20social-support%20programs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20extended%20project%2C%20expected%20to%20begin%20in%20February%20after%20a%20few-month%20pause%2C%20the%20first%20two%20groups%20will%20receive%20%241%2C000%20a%20month%20for%20six%20months%2C%20while%20the%20third%20group%20will%20receive%20%24100%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EBasic%20income%20can%20help%20prevent%20homelessness%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEver%20since%20high%20school%2C%20Laws%20has%20been%20a%20cook.%20It's%20what%20he's%20always%20been%20good%20at%2C%20he%20said%2C%20and%20it%20made%20him%20feel%20safe%20and%20productive.%20He%20never%20made%20a%20lot%20of%20money%20from%20cooking%2C%20but%20it%20allowed%20him%20to%20live%20somewhat%20comfortably.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202012%2C%20as%20a%20father%20of%20two%2C%20he%20lost%20nearly%20everything.%20His%20father%20died%20two%20years%20prior%2C%20and%20his%20breakup%20took%20a%20huge%20financial%20and%20mental%20toll%20on%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20never%20recovered%20fully%20from%20the%20bad%20breakup%2C%20I'm%20still%20suffering%20from%20parts%20of%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Laws%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20can't%20afford%20a%20home%2C%20and%20I%20still%20work%20full-time%20jobs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20had%20to%20continue%20working%20to%20support%20his%20children%20and%20pay%20off%20his%20car%2C%20and%20he%20said%20for%20six%20years%2C%20he%20lived%20in%20the%20parking%20lot%20of%20a%20restaurant%20as%20he%20couldn't%20afford%20rent%20and%20gas.%20After%20child%20support%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennial-gen-z-parents-struggle-lonely-childcare-costs-money-friends-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epayments%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20other%20expenses%2C%20he%20only%20received%20%24200%20every%20two%20weeks%20between%20his%20two%20jobs%2C%20but%20he%20kept%20making%20sacrifices%20for%20his%20kids'%20futures.%20He%20used%20whatever%20money%20he%20had%20left%20to%20get%20a%20hotel%20for%20himself%20and%20his%20kids%20on%20weekends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20alone%2C%20and%20I%20felt%20I%20had%20no%20help%20from%20anybody%2C%26quot%3B%20Laws%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20felt%20the%20world%20turn%20its%20back%20on%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELaws%20lost%20his%20cooking%20job%20at%20the%20start%20of%20the%20pandemic.%20He%20found%20work%20at%20a%20local%20Safeway%2C%20where%20he%20worked%20for%20three%20years%2C%20though%20he%20suffered%20a%20back%20injury%20that%20put%20him%20out%20of%20work%20again.%20He's%20since%20found%20a%20job%20at%20a%20hotel%20and%20briefly%20tried%20driving%20for%20Doordash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20his%20former%20coworkers%20found%20out%20he%20was%20living%20in%20his%20car%2C%20and%20they%20helped%20him%20find%20a%20place%20and%20pay%20rent.%20He%20saved%20up%20some%20money%20from%20his%20new%20job%20and%20got%20caught%20up%20on%20bills.%20Eventually%2C%20he%20needed%20to%20find%20a%20new%20place%20to%20live%2C%20and%20he%20couldn't%20find%20a%20situation%20that%20would%20work%20for%20him%20and%20his%20kids.%20After%20trying%20out%20living%20with%20roommates%2C%20he%20went%20back%20to%20living%20in%20his%20car.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20decade%2C%20Laws%20tried%20everything%20he%20could%20to%20keep%20going%20and%20be%20the%20best%20father%20he%20could.%20He%20sent%20in%20applications%20for%20financial%20assistance%20to%20various%20Denver-based%20organizations%2C%20asked%20everyone%20he%20knew%20about%20housing%20and%20career%20advancement%20opportunities%2C%20and%20did%20everything%20he%20could%20to%20get%20people%20to%20listen%20to%20his%20story.%20He%20couldn't%20find%20any%20programs%20for%20people%20in%20his%20situation%2C%20as%20many%20were%20catered%20to%20those%20recovering%20from%20drug%20addiction%20or%20with%20criminal%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20to%20no%20avail%20%E2%80%94%20until%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETurning%20his%20life%20around%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20years%20of%20applications%2C%20Laws%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fpgd.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFamily%20Promise%20of%20Greater%20Denver%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20organization%20that%20helps%20families%20experiencing%20or%20at%20risk%20of%20homelessness%2C%20and%20he%20was%20able%20to%20temporarily%20move%20into%20secure%20housing.%20His%20case%20manager%20told%20him%20about%20the%20DBIP%2C%20and%20he%20sent%20in%20an%20application.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20received%20%246%2C500%20upfront%2C%20followed%20by%20monthly%20payments%20of%20%24500.%20It%20allowed%20him%20to%20get%20an%20apartment%2C%20get%20furniture%2C%20eat%20healthier%2C%20and%20spend%20more%20time%20with%20his%20kids.%20He%20was%20also%20able%20to%20pick%20up%20another%20job%20to%20build%20up%20his%20savings.%20Throughout%20the%20project%2C%20he%20said%20he%20felt%20needed%20and%20supported%20by%20those%20around%20him%2C%20which%20gave%20him%20the%20desire%20to%20achieve%20something%20with%20his%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20was%20homeless%20before%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.denverbasicincomeproject.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDBIP%3C%2Fa%3E%20even%20accepted%20me%2C%20I%20had%20questioned%20myself%20if%20I%20was%20going%20to%20be%20a%20good%20father%20to%20my%20children%20because%20I%20was%20suffering%2C%26quot%3B%20Laws%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20got%20accepted%2C%20it%20changed%20my%20life.%20It%20brought%20joy%20to%20my%20heart%2C%20it%20brought%20me%20and%20my%20children%20together.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20year%2C%20he%20felt%20replenished%20and%20motivated%2C%20noting%20that%20he%20felt%20a%20greater%20sense%20of%20purpose.%20But%20the%20project%20ended%20last%20November%2C%20and%20he%20still%20didn't%20have%20the%20financial%20security%20he%20desired.%20He%20said%20he%20was%20grateful%20the%20project%20allowed%20him%20to%20maintain%20his%20work%20without%20as%20much%20stress%2C%20making%20the%20transition%20to%20life%20after%20the%20project%20a%20bit%20smoother.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20end%20of%20the%20program%20devastated%20me.%20The%20extra%20money%20I%20was%20getting%20each%20month%20was%20helping%20me%20pay%20for%20my%20rent%2C%20which%20wasn't%20a%20lot%20but%20it%20did%20help%2C%26quot%3B%20Laws%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20it%20ended%2C%20it%20kind%20of%20set%20me%20back%20a%20little%20bit%2C%20and%20I%20got%20evicted%20in%20November%20of%20last%20year.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELaws%20said%20shortly%20after%20the%20project%20ended%2C%20he%20went%20back%20to%20living%20in%20his%20car%20and%20became%20more%20depressed.%20He%20stopped%20Doordash%20driving%20because%20he%20said%20he%20wasn't%20making%20enough%20after%20taxes%20and%20other%20vehicle%20expenses%2C%20a%20problem%20many%20other%20drivers%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flyft-uber-gig-driving-with-disability-stock-flexibility-part-time-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehave%20shared%20with%20BI%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20he%20spent%20Christmas%20alone%20in%20his%20car%2C%20and%20though%20he%20was%20grateful%20for%20the%20support%20and%20encouragement%20he%20received%20during%20the%20project%2C%20it%20was%20tough%20to%20navigate%20life%20without%20financial%20assistance.%20He%20said%20he%20fears%20being%20forced%20to%20live%20in%20his%20car%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20his%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20suffered%20a%20major%20stroke%20in%20early%20January%2C%20and%20he%20had%20to%20drive%20himself%20to%20the%20hospital%20since%20there%20was%20nobody%20else%20to%20care%20for%20him.%20He%20spent%20a%20few%20days%20in%20the%20hospital%2C%20but%20he%20started%20right%20back%20to%20work%20afterward.%20He%20said%20he's%20been%20losing%20hope%20but%20keeps%20fighting%20daily%20for%20his%20kids.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20a%20father%2C%20I%20feel%20like%20I%20have%20to%20fight%20every%20day%20to%20survive%20and%20care%20for%20my%20kids%2C%20but%20it's%20hard%20to%20wake%20up%2C%20go%20to%20sleep%2C%26quot%3B%20Laws%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20hard%20to%20go%20on%20at%20this%20point.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20the%20DBIP's%20extension%2C%20Laws%20will%20receive%20another%20%241%2C000%20for%20six%20months%20starting%20in%20February%2C%20which%20he%20said%20will%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Bmiracle.%26quot%3B%20The%20extra%20money%20will%20allow%20him%20to%20get%20back%20on%20his%20feet%2C%20have%20more%20stability%2C%20and%20potentially%20get%20back%20into%20more%20stable%20housing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20should've%20seen%20the%20joy%20on%20my%20face%2C%26quot%3B%20Laws%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20felt%20so%20relieved.%20Some%20of%20the%20pressure%20came%20off%20of%20me.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdenver-guaranteed-basic-income-gbi-ubi-housing-security-homeless-rent-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706871901000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bbb45bac2de4f17ee691ed%3Ff