2C%20Liu%20saw%20a%20noticeable%20drop%20in%20his%20body%20fat%2C%20along%20with%20an%20increase%20in%20his%20strength%20and%20muscle%20mass.%20In%20total%2C%20he%20lost%20about%20nine%20pounds%2C%20accounting%20for%20gains%20in%20muscle%20mass%2C%20but%20shed%20seven%20inches%20off%20his%20waistline.%20In%20the%20process%2C%20he%20added%20more%20than%2050%20pounds%20onto%20his%20lifts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20think%20it's%20like%20starvation%2C%20or%20that%20everyone%20must%20be%20on%20a%20low%20carb%20diet%20or%20doing%20tons%20of%20cardio%20but%20it's%20actually%20quite%20the%20opposite%20%E2%80%94high%20carb%2C%20not%20a%20lot%20of%20cardio%2C%20and%20weight%20training.%26quot%3B%20Enaz%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELiu%2C%20who%20lives%20in%20London%2C%20said%20the%20most%20striking%20part%20of%20his%20fitness%20journey%20was%20that%20his%20best%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-make-the-most-gains-short-workout-science-2022-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efitness%20progress%3C%2Fa%3E%20came%20from%20doing%20less%2C%20not%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20focusing%20on%20basics%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-protein-maximize-muscle-gains-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeating%20enough%20protein%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20consistent%2C%20full-body%20strength%20training%2C%20Liu%20said%20his%20routine%20was%20easier%2C%20less%20stressful%2C%20and%20paid%20off%20by%20revealing%20the%20muscle%20definition%20and%20ab%20visibility%20he%20was%20told%20he'd%20never%20get.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20never%20been%20so%20big%20and%20so%20broad%2C%20and%20this%20is%20the%20first%20time%20in%20my%20life%20I've%20seen%20my%20abs%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20have%20more%20energy%20and%20a%20better%20mood%20too.%20It's%20more%20about%20feeling%20better%20and%20more%20confident%20than%20just%20looking%20good.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHe%20wanted%20to%20gain%20muscle%2C%20build%20strength%2C%20and%20lose%20belly%20fat%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20many%20gymgoers%2C%20Liu%20wanted%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-rock-eccentric-exercise-science-says-can-build-muscle-fast-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eput%20on%20muscle%20mass%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20also%20trim%20some%20body%20fat%2C%20especially%20around%20his%20belly%2C%20to%20get%20a%20lean%2C%20athletic%20look.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20main%20goal%20was%20to%20get%20bigger%2C%20and%20gain%20muscle.%20I've%20always%20had%20a%20bit%20of%20body%20fat%20so%20you%20can't%20really%20see%20any%20tone%20or%20definition%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPreviously%2C%20Liu%20had%20bad%20experiences%20with%20personal%20trainers%20who%20bombarded%20him%20with%20information%20on%20what%20he%20needed%20to%20do%20and%20avoid%20to%20meet%20his%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20overloaded%20me%20with%20metrics.%20I%20had%20so%20much%20to%20do%2C%20it%20was%20very%20stressful%20and%20it%20was%20hard%20to%20sustain%2C%26quot%3B%20Liu%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20measuring%20like%2020%20things%20on%20an%20Excel%20sheet.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Enaz%20initially%20told%20him%20to%20cut%20back%20his%20complex%20list%20of%20to-dos%2C%20Liu%20was%20skeptical.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20first%2C%20I%20was%20like%2C%20surely%20there's%20more%20to%20it%20than%20this%3F%20Is%20that%20all%3F%26quot%3B%20Liu%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20within%20weeks%2C%20Liu%20said%20he%20had%20already%20begun%20burning%20belly%20fat%20and%20seeing%20more%20muscle%20definition%2C%20motivating%20him%20to%20keep%20sticking%20to%20the%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHe%20works%20out%20four%20times%20a%20week%20with%20full-body%20strength%20exercises.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELiu%20still%20works%20with%20Enaz%2C%20meeting%20with%20him%20in%20person%20once%20weekly%20to%20check%20in%2C%20and%20completes%20the%20rest%20of%20his%20sessions%20on%20his%20own%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20hits%20the%20gym%20four%20times%20a%20week%2C%20focusing%20primarily%20on%20strength%20training%20with%20little%20to%20no%20cardio.%20Each%20session%20works%20the%20full%20body%20and%20takes%20about%20an%20hour%20(including%20time%20waiting%20to%20use%20equipment%20in%20the%20public%20gym).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELiu%20said%20about%20half%20his%20exercises%20are%20compound%20movements%20like%20deadlifts%20and%20bench%20presses%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiit-style-combination-exercises-not-good-for-muscle-building-trainer-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ework%20all%20the%20muscles%20at%20once%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20half%20target%20specific%20muscle%20groups%2C%20such%20as%20preacher%20curls%20for%20the%20biceps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20performs%20three%20sets%20of%20each%20exercise%2C%20and%20up%20to%2012%20reps%20per%20set%2C%20with%20two%20minutes%20of%20rest%20between%20sets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20time%20he%20can%20easily%20do%2012%20reps%2C%20he%20increases%20weight%20(doing%20fewer%20reps%20if%20needed)%2C%20a%20key%20principle%20of%20gains%20known%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprogressive-overload-fitness-meaning-and-how-to-do-it-2021-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprogressive%20overload%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20Liu%20started%20by%20doing%2012%20reps%20of%2030%20pounds%20on%20the%20shoulder%20press%2C%20and%20now%20does%2010%20reps%20with%2066%20pounds.%20He%20also%20added%20almost%2070%20pounds%20to%20his%20bench%20press%20with%20this%20method.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELiu%20said%20the%20amount%20of%20work%20felt%20just%20right%2C%20when%20previously%20his%20assigned%20workouts%20felt%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmuscle-building-cut-junk-volume-less-exercise-more-gains-expert-2022-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etoo%20much%20effort%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20not%20enough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20achievable%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20tired%20enough%20but%20not%20overtired.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHe%20counts%20macros%20and%20started%20eating%20more%20protein%2C%20but%20didn't%20cut%20any%20foods%20out%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELiu%20said%20his%20diet%20is%20flexible%2C%20and%20breaks%20down%20into%20about%2035%25%20of%20calories%20from%20protein%2C%2040%25%20from%20carbohydrates%2C%20and%2025%25%20from%20fats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20he%20said%20Enaz%20has%20gradually%20decreased%20his%20calorie%20goal%20so%20he%20can%20continue%20burning%20fat%20while%20still%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-not-eating-enough-to-build-muscle-sports-dietitian-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeating%20enough%20to%20build%20muscle%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20that%20guideline%2C%20Liu%20said%20he%20can%20eat%20what%20he%20likes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20long%20as%20I%20follow%20the%20calories%20and%20macros%2C%20I%20haven't%20cut%20out%20any%20foods%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELiu%20said%20the%20biggest%20difference%20in%20his%20eating%20habits%20has%20been%20getting%20more%20protein%2C%20including%20a%20protein%20shake%20and%20a%20scoop%20of%20protein%20powder%20with%20his%20morning%20oatmeal.%20That%2C%20and%20he's%20stopped%20stressing%20about%20strict%2C%20arbitrary%20rules%20around%20what%20he%20can%20or%20can't%20eat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20been%20simple%20and%20focused.%20I%20followed%20it%2C%20learned%20from%20it%2C%20and%20I'm%20able%20to%20keep%20doing%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Liu%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmore-energy-defined-abs-simplify-workout-do-less-2024-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706869