0from%20Austin%20to%20New%20York%20City%20in%201985%2C%20and%20then%20to%20Houston%20in%201990.%20When%20I%20arrived%20in%20Houston%2C%20Ann%20Richards%20was%20the%20governor%20of%20Texas%2C%20and%20the%20city%20had%20a%20female%20mayor%20and%20police%20chief.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201995%2C%20I%20left%20Houston%20and%20moved%20back%20to%20Austin.%20By%20the%20time%20I%20left%20the%20city%20in%202019%2C%20there%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.expressnews.com%2Fnews%2Flocal%2Farticle%2FTexas-women-local-government-17056432.php%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eonly%20a%20few%20female%20leaders%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Texas.%20At%20that%20point%2C%20it%20seemed%20like%20the%20liberal%20advances%20women%20had%20made%20in%20the%20state%20were%20really%20constricting.%20Policies%20made%20on%20gender%20and%20minority%20rights%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20proliferation%20of%20guns%2C%20were%20also%20concerning%20to%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20thought%20Washington%20state%20would%20be%20a%20better%20place%20for%20me%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20I%20moved%20to%20Washington%20because%20it%20was%20more%20liberal%20politically%2C%20and%2C%20similar%20to%20Texas%2C%20there%20is%20no%20state%20income%20tax.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20that%20point%2C%20I%20had%20been%20single%20for%20many%20years%2C%20so%20I%20made%20the%20trip%20all%20by%20myself.%20I%20loaded%20all%20my%20furniture%20into%20a%20big%20U-Haul%20truck%20and%20attached%20my%20car%20to%20a%20trailer%20in%20the%20back.%20My%20two%20dogs%20joined%20me%20in%20the%20cab%20of%20the%20truck%2C%20and%20we%20took%20a%20five-day%20journey%20from%20Austin%20to%20Port%20Angeles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221367%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Coquihalla%20Highway%20in%20British%20Columbia.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bab23c7a3d271488765df4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22716%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECoquihalla%20Highway%20in%20British%20Columbia.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Linda%20Ofshe%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20COVID%20struck%2C%20so%20I%20couldn't%20go%20out%20and%20meet%20new%20people.%20Instead%2C%20I%20joined%20a%20dating%20site%20and%20set%20a%2060-mile%20radius%20for%20potential%20matches.%20I%20met%20a%20Canadian%20and%20we%20started%20a%20telephone%20and%20Zoom%20relationship.%20We%20later%20fell%20in%20love.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%202021%2C%20we%20met%20for%20the%20first%20time%20at%20Peace%20Arch%20Park%20in%20Washington.%20After%20the%20visit%2C%20we%20went%20back%20to%20our%20respective%20countries%20and%20continued%20to%20get%20to%20know%20each%20other.%20When%20the%20borders%20opened%2C%20we%20got%20married%20that%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20moved%20to%20Canada%2C%20and%20I'm%20not%20looking%20back%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20moved%20to%20British%20Columbia%20two%20years%20ago.%20He%20sponsored%20me%20in%20getting%20my%20permanent%20residency%2C%20which%20I%20received%20last%20August.%20It%20was%20a%20pretty%20quick%20process%20that%20took%20only%20about%2010%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20live%20in%20Victoria%2C%20which%20is%20a%20small%20city%20that%20is%20right%20across%20the%20strait%20of%20Juan%20de%20Fuca%20from%20Port%20Angeles.%20Flowers%20bloom%20all%20year%20round%20here%2C%20and%20the%20area%20has%20a%20sub-Mediterranean%20climate.%20I%20can%20see%20the%20Olympic%20Mountains%20from%20my%20living%20room%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20just%20absolutely%20beautiful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221427%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Pemberton%20Mountains%20in%20British%20Columbia.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bab249ac2de4f17ee669bc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221074%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPemberton%20Mountains%20in%20British%20Columbia.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Linda%20Ofshe%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20live%20in%20a%20three-bedroom%2C%20two-bathroom%20duplex%20that%20we%20rent%20for%20%243%2C000%20Canadian%20dollars%20(about%20%242%2C235)%20each%20month.%20Rents%20are%20expensive%20here%20%E2%80%94%20but%20rents%20are%20also%20expensive%20in%20Washington%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20still%20own%20a%20duplex%20in%20Austin%2C%20and%20for%20retirement%20income%2C%20I%20rent%20out%20both%20sides%20for%20about%20%241%2C700%20each%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22633%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Linda%20Ofshe's%20Austin%20duplex.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bab3807a3d271488765ebf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOfshe's%20Austin%20duplex.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Linda%20Ofshe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGas%20is%20very%20expensive%20in%20Canada%3B%20they%20sell%20it%20by%20the%20liter.%20So%2C%20if%20it%20says%20%241.53%2C%20that's%20like%20%245%20and%20some%20change%20per%20gallon.%20Coming%20from%20Texas%2C%20which%20has%20really%20low%20gas%20prices%2C%20it's%20a%20lot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20cheap%20gas%2C%20I%20miss%20the%20HEB%20grocery%20store%20chain.%20I'm%20sorry%20to%20say%20that%20is%20the%20one%20thing%20I%20miss%20more%20than%20my%20friends.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20love%20it%20here%20%E2%80%94%20but%20Canada%20isn't%20perfect%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20turns%20out%20Canada%20is%20a%20little%20better%20than%20the%20United%20States%20on%20climate%2C%20safety%2C%20and%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20some%20extreme%20politics%20here%2C%20too%2C%20but%20they%20haven't%20taken%20over%20like%20they%20did%20in%20the%20States.%20The%20climate%20here%20is%20a%20lot%20cooler%2C%20of%20course%2C%20and%20safety%20is%20better%20because%20they%20don't%20allow%20everyone%20to%20carry%20a%20gun.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20healthcare%20is%20a%20national%20concern%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20living%20in%20Texas%2C%20I%20didn't%20know%20much%20about%20Canada%2C%20except%20that%20they%20had%20universal%20healthcare%2C%20and%20I%20thought%2C%20'Wow%2C%20that's%20great.'%20But%20once%20I%20got%20here%2C%20as%20an%20older%20person%20relying%20on%20healthcare%2C%20I%20do%20have%20concerns%20about%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20found%20out%20there's%20a%20shortage%20of%20family%20doctors%20%E2%80%94%20what%20Americans%20would%20call%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eprimary%20care%20physicians.%20So%2C%20you%20can%20get%20an%20appointment%20at%20a%20clinic%2C%20but%20you%20may%20not%20get%20the%20same%20doctor%20next%20time%20you%20visit.%20I've%20also%20read%20articles%20about%20there%20being%20terrible%20waits%20at%20the%20emergency%20room.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22664%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Ofshe%20and%20her%20partner.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65bab2657a3d271488765e12%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22498%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOfshe%20and%20her%20partner.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Linda%20Ofshe%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20my%20medical%20concerns%2C%20I'm%20happier%20in%20Canada%20than%20I%20was%20in%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20being%20single%20for%20decades%2C%20I'm%20married%20to%20a%20wonderful%20man%20who%20loves%20me%20very%20much.%20And%20because%20I'm%20retired%2C%20we%20go%20camping%20and%20see%20the%20most%20beautiful%20places%20that%20I%20never%20knew%20existed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20food%20here%20is%20just%20as%20good%20as%20it%20was%20in%20New%20York%20City%20and%20Houston%2C%20which%20are%20considered%20among%20the%20best%20cities%20for%20great%20restaurants.%20The%20people%20here%20are%20also%20wonderful%2C%20warm%2C%20and%20open.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20life%20has%20greatly%20improved%20leaving%20the%20States%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20intend%20to%20ever%20live%20in%20Texas%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomer-moved-to-canada-retirement-weather-love-202