0and%20founding%20director%20of%20the%20Centre%20for%20Economic%20Data%20and%20Analysis%20(CEDA)%20at%20Ashoka%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20recipients%20of%20the%20award%20are%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDanny%20Quah%2C%20NUS%3Cbr%3E%5CnMarc%20Melitz%2C%20Harvard%20University%3Cbr%3E%5CnSam%20Bowles%2C%20Santa%20Fe%20Institute%3Cbr%3E%5CnEkaterina%20Zhuravskaya%2C%20Paris%20School%20of%20Economics%3Cbr%3E%5CnAdam%20Szeidl%2C%20Central%20European%20University%3Cbr%3E%5CnVera%20Songwe%2C%20UN%20Africa%3Cbr%3E%5CnGordon%20Hanson%2C%20Harvard%20University%3Cbr%3E%5CnSascha%20Becker%2C%20Monash%20University%3Cbr%3E%5CnIndermit%20Singh%20Gill%2C%20World%20Bank%3Cbr%3E%5CnMiaojie%20Yu%2C%20Liaoning%20University%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IEA%20was%20founded%20in%201950%20as%20a%20non-governmental%20organisation%2C%20as%20part%20of%20a%20UNESCO-driven%20initiative.%20The%20IEA%20is%20governed%20by%20a%20council%2C%20composed%20of%20representatives%20of%20its%20member%20associations%20and%20some%20co-opted%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20of%20its%20past%20presidents%20are%20Amartya%20Sen%20(1986%E2%80%931989)%20and%20Kaushik%20Basu%20(2017-2021).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fellow%20award%20recipients%20are%20selected%20by%20a%20Nominating%20Committee%20which%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Association%2C%20takes%20it%20upon%20itself%20to%20%E2%80%9Censure%20regional%20diversity%20and%20gender%20balance.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706852747000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02105558%2FUntitled-design-2-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fjayati-ghosh-ashwini-deshpande-international-economic-association-fellow-awards%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20annual%20fellowship%20is%20awarded%20to%2010%20'economists%20worldwide%20who%20have%20made%20an%20important%20contribution%20through%20the%20creation%20or%20dissemination%20of%20new%20ideas%20and%20high-quality%20policy%20work.'%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fjayati-ghosh-ashwini-deshpande-international-economic-association-fellow-awards%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Watch%3A%20Bajrang%20Dal%20Leader%20Arrested%20For%20Cow%20Slaughter%2C%20Hatched%20Conspiracy%20to%20Implicate%20Muslim%20Man%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02111015%2FScreenshot-2024-02-02-at-11.09.38-AM.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EFour%20people%20including%20Moradabad%20district%20president%20of%20Bajrang%20Dal%20Monu%20Bishnoi%20have%20been%20arrested%20by%20the%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20Police%20for%20slaughtering%20a%20cow%20and%20trying%20to%20implicate%20a%20Muslim%20man%20in%20a%20false%20case.%20They%20have%20also%20been%20accused%20of%20conspiring%20against%20the%20police.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolice%20allege%20that%20one%20of%20the%20accused%2C%20Shahabuddin%2C%20took%20the%20help%20of%20the%20Bajrang%20Dal%20workers%20to%20put%20a%20man%20named%20Mehmood%20in%20jail%20by%20making%20it%20look%20like%20he%20had%20killed%20cows.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20January%2016%2C%20the%20head%20of%20a%20cow%20was%20discovered%20on%20a%20road%20frequented%20by%20Hindu%20pilgrims.%20On%20the%20night%20of%20January%2028%2C%20another%20cow%20slaughter%20incident%20took%20place.%20The%20police%20found%20both%20these%20incidents%20suspicious.%20At%20the%20site%20of%20the%20second%20incident%2C%20Mehmood%E2%80%99s%20wallet%20was%20found%20in%20a%20pair%20of%20trousers%20lying%20on%20the%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhen%20Mehmood%20was%20interrogated%2C%20he%20told%20that%20he%20had%20enmity%20with%20some%20people%20in%20the%20village%2C%20due%20to%20which%20an%20attempt%20was%20made%20to%20implicate%20him.%20The%20names%20of%20Shahabuddin%20and%20Jamshed%20came%20up.%20These%20people%20took%20the%20help%20of%20Monu%20Bishnoi%2C%20Rajiv%20Chaudhary%20and%20Raman%20Chaudhary%20to%20send%20their%20opponent%20to%20jail%2C%E2%80%9D%20Hemraj%20Meena%2C%20Senior%20Superintendent%20of%20Police%20(SSP)%2C%20Moradabad%2C%20told%20the%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBajrang%20Dal%E2%80%99s%20Monu%20Bishnoi%20was%20recently%20in%20jail%20in%20an%20attempt%20to%20murder%20case.%20Post-release%2C%20Bishnoi%20engaged%20in%20illegal%20activities%2C%20attempting%20to%20manipulate%20the%20Chhajlait%20police%20station%2C%20and%20when%20officials%20resisted%2C%20he%20devised%20this%20trap.%20The%20police%2C%20employing%20electronic%20surveillance%20and%20mobile%20location%20data%2C%20unraveled%20the%20conspiracy%2C%20resulting%20in%20FIRs%20filed%20under%20various%20IPC%20sections%20and%20the%20Cow%20Slaughter%20Act.%20Two%20accused%20are%20still%20at%20large.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBishnoi%20allegedly%20exerted%20significant%20pressure%20on%20the%20police%20for%20his%20ulterior%20motives.%20Failing%20to%20garner%20cooperation%20from%20the%20officials%2C%20he%20purportedly%20devised%20a%20plan%20to%20frame%20Mehmood%2C%20creating%20pressure%20on%20the%20police%20to%20yield%20to%20his%20demands.%20The%20orchestrated%20incidents%20aimed%20to%20force%20compliance%20from%20law%20enforcement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FvXGC5_s7ujY%3Fsi%3Dl5Br6RLwTv6ap3lJ%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706852474000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02111015%2FScreenshot-2024-02-02-at-11.09.38-AM.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fwatch-bajrang-dal-leader-arrested-for-cow-slaughter-hatched-conspiracy-to-implicate-muslim-man%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Bajrang%20Dal's%20Monu%20Bishnoi%20has%20been%20accused%20of%20trying%20to%20manipulate%20the%20police.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fwatch-bajrang-dal-leader-arrested-for-cow-slaughter-hatched-conspiracy-to-implicate-muslim-man%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%202%20days%2C%20Paytm%20erases%20%242%20bn%20in%20market%20value%20as%20RBI%20action%20spooks%20market%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706852027000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2024-02%2F02%2Ffull%2F1706851938-106.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fin-2-days-paytm-erases-2-bn-in-market-value-as-rbi-action-spooks-market-124020200305_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Paytm%20is%20now%20down%20about%2077%20per%20cent%20from%20its%20initial%20public%20offering%20in%202021%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fin-2-days-paytm-erases-2-bn-in-market-value-as-rbi-action-spooks-market-124020200305_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fin-2-days-paytm-erases-2-bn-in-market-value-as-rbi-action-spooks-market-124020200305_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fin-2-days-paytm-erases-2-bn-in-market-value-as-rbi-action-spooks-market-124020200305_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20the%20Study%20of%20Dalit%20Religions%20Is%20Necessary%20to%20Understand%20Hindu%20Majoritarianism%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02103518%2FScreenshot-2024-02-02-at-10.33.5.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EJoel%20Lee%E2%80%99s%20book%20%3Cem%3EDeceptive%20Majority%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20an%20erudite%20addition%20to%20the%20study%20of%20Indian%20religions%20in%20general%20and%20Dalit%20religions%20in%20particular.%20It%20charts%20the%20complex%20relationship%20of%20Dalits%20and%20Dalit%20religions%20with%20Hinduism%20and%20Hindu%20majoritarianism%20in%20colonial%20and%20postcolonial%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20archival%20research%20and%20ethnography%2C%20Lee%20explores%20the%20contradictory%20nature%20of%20latent%20and%20manifest%20religion%20of%20sanitation%20labour%20castes%20from%20the%20583%20clans%20of%20the%20Awadh%20region.%20The%20book%20explores%20the%20making%20of%20the%20Valmiki%20identity%20under%20colonial%20modernity%20of%20the%20sanitation%20labour%20castes%20of%20Awadh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHinduism%2C%20their%20declamatory%20religion%2C%20is%20posed%20against%20the%20Lal%20Begi%20tradition%20that%20functions%20as%20an%20underground%20religion.%20Instead%20of%20following%20the%20well-trodden%20and%20rigid%20conceptual%20path%20of%20identity%20and%20recognition%2C%20Lee%20draws%20out%20the%20conceptual%20possibilities%20of%20%3Cem%3Epahcha%CC%84n%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20explores%20the%20politics%20of%20pahcha%CC%84n.%20Pahcha%CC%84n%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdistinguishing%20mark%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20sign%20by%20which%20a%20person%20or%20group%20is%20recognised%20by%20others%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02094844%2F9781108843829-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22256%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-695318%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22385%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EDeceptive%20Majority%3A%20Dalits%2C%20Hinduism%20and%20Underground%20Religion%2C%20Joel%20Lee%2C%20Cambridge%20University%20Press%2C%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20concept%2C%20then%2C%20pahcha%CC%84n%20directs%20attention%20to%20the%20semiotic%20terrain%20on%20which%20identitarian%20struggle%20takes%20place%20and%20the%20malleability%20of%20the%20signs%20on%20which%20recognition%20depends.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChapter%20Two%20is%20a%20peek%20into%20the%20pre-enumerative%20Lal%20Begi%20religion%20of%20Chuhras%20(Mehters%20or%20Halalkhors).%20Through%20his%20reading%20of%20archives%2C%20Lee%20moves%20beyond%20the%20limiting%20accounts%20of%20conversions%20and%20syncretism.%20Lal%20Begi%20was%20indeed%20asserted%20as%20a%20religion%20different%20from%20Hindus%20and%20Muslims%20and%20could%20be%20easily%20distinguished%20in%20soteriological%20terms.%20Hindu%20and%20to%20a%20certain%20extent%20Muslim%20were%20terms%20that%20were%20contrasting%20rather%20than%20encompassing%20Dalit%20communities.%20While%20there%20was%20a%20brotherhood%20of%20sorts%20between%20Lal%20Begis%20and%20Muslims%2C%20the%20idolatry%20involved%20amongst%20Lal%20Begis%20did%20not%20make%20them%20fellow%20Muslims.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBroadly%20this%20chapter%20reiterates%20that%20Dalits%20were%20neither%20Hindus%20not%20Muslims%20and%20Lal%20Begis%20were%20not%20%E2%80%98Bal%20Mikis%E2%80%99.%20The%20imperial%20government%E2%80%99s%20decision%20to%20enumerate%20%E2%80%98untouchables%E2%80%99%20as%20Hindu%20by%20default%20was%20even%20opposed%20by%20Hindu%20officials%20implementing%20the%20census%20initially.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20politics%20of%20majoritarianism%20that%20followed%20enumerative%20politics%20produced%20Lal%20Begis%20and%20broadly%20untouchables%20as%20Hindus.%20Outcastes%20could%20however%20generate%20only%20%3Cem%3Eghr%CC%A3n%CC%A3a%CC%84%3C%2Fem%3E%20(disgust)%20for%20Hindus%20and%20making%20them%20Hindus%20involved%20purification%20(%3Cem%3Eshuddhi%3C%2Fem%3E)%20and%20a%20struggle%20with%20ghr%CC%A3n%CC%A3a%CC%84.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChapter%20Three%20provides%20deep%20insights%20into%20the%20politics%20of%20shuddhi%20pursued%20by%20the%20Arya%20Samaj%20and%20Shraddhanand%20and%20its%20critical%20role%20in%20diverting%20ghr%CC%A3n%CC%A3a%CC%84%20towards%20Muslims%20while%20mobilising%20sympathy%20towards%20sanitation%20castes%20as%20Valmikis%20(long%20lost%20brothers).%20The%20scavenger%20castes%20came%20to%20bear%20lineage%20with%20sage%20Valmiki%20as%20part%20of%20shuddhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Hinduism%20is%20framed%20as%20a%20civil%20religion%20under%20Hindutva%20in%20contemporary%20times%20(Waghmore%2C%202022)%2C%20Lee%20helps%20us%20recollect%20the%20foundations%20of%20majoritarian%20politics%20and%20processes%20in%20Hindu%20missionary%20majoritarianism%20of%20the%20Arya%20Samaj%20followed%20by%20trustee%20majoritarianism%20of%20Gandhi.%20Arya%20Samaj%E2%80%99s%20competition%20with%20Christian%20Missionaries%20produced%20shuddhi%20as%20an%20emergent%20answer%20where%20the%20Gayatri%20mantra%20or%20fire%20sacrifice%20could%20enable%20the%20entry%20of%20non-Hindus%20into%20Arya%20Dharma.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fbihar-caste-survey-the-whos-who-in-the-data-lalbegi%5C%22%3EBihar%20Caste%20Survey%3A%20The%20Who%E2%80%99s%20Who%20in%20the%20Data%20%7C%20Lalbegi%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChapter%20Four%20engages%20with%20trustee%20majoritarianism%20of%20Gandhi%20and%20the%20Harijan%20Sevak%20Sangh.%20Gandhi%20would%20oppose%20%3Cem%3Eshuddhi%3C%2Fem%3E%20to%20insist%20that%20%E2%80%98untouchables%E2%80%99%20were%20always%20Hindus%20and%20there%20was%20no%20need%20to%20purify%20them%2C%20scavenging%20was%20fulfilment%20of%20their%20caste%20dharma%20and%20that%20he%20%5Bpure%20castes%5D%20was%20the%20sole%20trustee%20of%20untouchables.%20For%20Gandhi%2C%20change%20for%20outcastes%20could%20be%20driven%20only%20by%20Hindu%20benevolence%20and%20not%20Depressed%20Class%20assertion.%20Several%20luminaries%20including%20Rabindranath%20Tagore%20would%20join%20to%20defend%20Gandhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20Harijan%20Sevak%20Sangh%2C%20like%20Shraddhanand%2C%20pedalled%20the%20myth%20that%20Muslims%20built%20the%20latrines%20and%20Bhangi%20was%3Cbr%3E%5Cnessentially%20a%20recent%20product%20of%20urban%20life%20first%20created%20by%20Muslims.%20The%20face-off%20between%20Ambedkar%20and%20Gandhi%20was%20also%20a%20clash%20between%20the%20assertion%20of%20Depressed%20Classes%20and%20Hindu%20benevolence%20where%20Gandhi%20insisted%20that%20Ambedkar%20in%20accepting%20the%20Poona%20Pact%20was%20also%20accepting%20that%20he%20and%20his%20followers%20were%20%E2%80%98Hindus%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20alterity%20of%20Lal%20Begis%20came%20under%20severe%20check%20with%20the%20Scheduled%20Caste%20Order%20of%201950%20as%20no%20person%20who%20professes%20a%20religion%20different%20from%20the%20Hindu%20religion%20was%20to%20be%20deemed%20a%20Scheduled%20Caste.%20Their%20Muslim%20sounding%20names%20and%20Lal%20Begi%20religion%20could%20not%20fit%20the%20modernist%20slots%20of%20enumeration%20%E2%80%93%20Hindu%20and%20Muslim.%20They%20could%20either%20reap%20benefits%20of%20Hindu%20benevolence%20or%20stick%20to%20the%20Lal%20Begi%20tradition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChapter%20Five%20on%20the%20making%20of%20a%20Valmiki%20identity%20is%20based%20primarily%20on%20interviews%20with%20elderly%20respondents%20in%20Lucknow.%20Lee%20suggests%20that%20reaping%20benefits%20of%20Hindu%20benevolence%20and%20Hinduisation%20was%20not%20necessarily%20Sanskritization%20and%20the%20process%20of%20Valmikisation%20was%20always%20fraught%20with%20the%20Lal%20Begi%20challenge%20from%20within.%20Dissuading%20scavenger%20castes%20from%20Lal%20Begi%20Ummat%20involved%20not%20merely%20giving%20up%20names%20and%20old%20tradition%20but%20raking%20up%20the%20cohabitation%20controversy%20to%20%E2%80%98reclaim%E2%80%99%20scavenger%20caste%20women%20who%20were%20either%20living%20or%20married%20to%20Muslim%20men.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELal%20Beg%20came%20to%20be%20Muslim%20and%20because%20Valmikis%20were%20not%20Muslims%2C%20they%20had%20to%20therefore%20dig%20up%20shrines%20of%20their%20pir%2C%20Lal%20Beg%20Sahib.%20As%20Lal%20Begis%20became%20Valmikis%20they%20also%20dropped%20Muslim%20sounding%20names%20so%20as%20to%20be%20eligible%20for%20state%20education%20and%20jobs%20meant%20for%20Scheduled%20Castes.%20Hinduisation%20of%20Lal%20Begis%20encompassed%20culinary%20and%20other%20aspects%20of%20social%20life%20and%20involved%20conflict%20between%20traditionalists%20and%20reformists.%20It%20was%20not%20however%20a%20complete%20Hinduisation%20or%20Sanskritisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Chapter%20Six%2C%20Lee%E2%80%99s%20detailed%20ethnography%20elaborates%20how%20Hinduism%20is%20more%20of%20a%20declamatory%20religion%20for%20scavenger%20castes%20in%20Lucknow%20meant%20to%20reap%20wages%20of%20their%20limited%20political%20inclusion%20while%20socially%20they%20continue%20to%20be%20excluded.%20The%20Jhanki%20and%20Valmiki%20Jayantis%20of%20mainstream%20Hindu%20parties%20(Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20and%20Congress)%20are%20contrasted%20in%20Chapter%20Seven%20with%20the%20thriving%20%3Cem%3Eummat%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20Lal%20Beg.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20provided%20with%20ethnographic%20details%20of%20annual%20Jamghat%20ritual%20and%20celebration%20of%20sacrifice%20where%20Muslims%20(Hajjam%20to%20Pathan)%20perform%20the%20sacrifice.%20Lee%20draws%20parallels%20between%20the%20underground%20Lal%20Begi%20practices%20with%20Taqiyya%20of%20Shias%2C%20as%20both%20are%20a%20product%20of%3Cbr%3E%5Cnrepresentational%20violence.%20Taqiyya%20is%20a%20belief%20that%20allows%20a%20follower%20of%20Islam%20to%20deny%20their%20faith%20in%20the%20face%20of%20persecution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDeceit%2C%20after%20all%2C%20is%20essential%20to%20human%20interaction%2C%20from%20the%20little%20white%20lies%20of%20which%20everyday%20politeness%20consists%20to%20the%20great%20collective%20self-deceptions%20that%20enable%20us%20to%20ignore%20burning%20contradictions%20in%20cultural%20life.%20That%20Taqiyya%20is%20more%20self-aware%20than%20some%20practices%20of%20truth%20concealment%20does%20not%20make%20it%20impossible%20to%20analyse.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Orientalist%20stereotype%20of%20Taqiyya%20as%20%E2%80%9Cfrivolous%20hypocrisy%2C%E2%80%9D%20for%20its%20part%2C%20can%20be%20addressed%20by%20critically%20attending%20to%20the%20conditions%20of%3Cbr%3E%5Cnknowledge%20production%20under%20which%20it%20emerged%2C%20circulated%2C%20and%20acquired%20%E2%80%9Cauthority.%E2%80%9D%20The%20most%20difficult%20obstacle%20to%20a%20clear-eyed%20study%20of%20Taqiyya%2C%20perhaps%2C%20is%20acknowledging%20as%20parochial%20the%20moral%20assumptions%20about%20secrecy%20and%20publicity%20that%20pass%20as%20universal%20in%20modernity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20theory%2C%20though%2C%20just%20as%20with%20other%20ideological%20axioms%20we%20hold%20dear%2C%20we%20should%20be%20able%2C%20having%20acknowledged%20them%2C%20to%20suspend%20the%20moral%20assessments%20they%20animate%20for%20the%20purposes%20of%20analysis.%20If%20we%20do%20this%2C%20we%20may%20be%20able%20to%20perceive%20in%20the%20doctrine%20of%20Taqiyya%20something%20other%20than%20what%20recent%20centuries%20of%20Protestant%20hegemony%20have%20prepared%20us%20to%20perceive.%20(pp.%20270%E2%80%93271)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20epilogue%2C%20Lee%20emphasises%20the%20need%20to%20study%20the%20everyday%20production%20of%20neighbourliness%20and%20the%20non-commission%20of%20violence%20to%20understand%20the%20quietly%20thriving%20neighbourly%20interdependence.%20The%20Indian%20concept%20of%20pahcha%CC%84n%20could%20indeed%20help%20us%20turn%20the%20Euro-American%20scholarly%20apparatus%20upside%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20experience-near%2C%20north%20Indian%20vernacular%20concept%20of%20pahcha%CC%84n%2C%20I%20have%20maintained%2C%20offers%20analytical%20leverage%20on%20the%20actually%20occurring%20politics%20of%20caste%20and%20religion%20in%20a%20way%20that%20these%20ideas%20of%20global%20anglophone%20social%20thought%20do%20not.%20%5B%E2%80%A6%5D%20In%20an%20account%20conceptually%20guided%20by%20pahcha%CC%84n%2C%20it%20is%20possible%20to%20see%20how%20the%20majoritarian%20project%20can%20enjoy%20triumph%20and%20suffer%20defraudment%20at%20one%3Cbr%3E%5Cnand%20the%20same%20time%20%E2%80%93%20these%20processes%20develop%20along%20divergent%20semiotic%20channels%3B%20the%20adept%20semiotician%20communicates%20pahcha%CC%84n%20differently%20by%20means%20of%20different%20classes%20of%20signs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJoel%20Lee%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EDeceptive%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EMajority%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20an%20excellent%20contribution%20to%20the%20study%20of%20caste%2C%20religion%2C%20and%20most%20of%20all%20of%20one%20of%20the%20most%20under-studied%20and%20marginalised%20social%20groups%20in%20north%20India.%20Outcaste%20lifeworlds%20may%20indeed%20present%20critical%20possibilities%20for%20the%20study%20of%20neighbourliness%20due%20to%20the%20embodied%20otherness%20of%20%E2%80%98untouchables%E2%80%99%20in%20relation%20to%20Hinduism.%20Beyond%20the%20study%20of%20outcastes%2C%20what%20promise%20and%20critical%20insights%20will%20the%20concept%20of%20pahcha%CC%84n%20offer%20in%20the%20study%20of%20Hinduism%20and%20new%20Hindutva%3F%20This%20remains%20to%20be%20seen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESuryakant%20Waghmore%20is%20a%20professor%20of%20sociology%20at%20IIT%20Bombay.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706851128000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F02103518%2FScreenshot-2024-02-02-at-10.33.5.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fbook-review-joel-lee-deceptive-majority%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Based%20on%20archival%20research%20and%20ethnography%2C%20Joel%20Lee%20explores%20the%20contradictory%20nature%20of%20the%20latent%20and%20manifest%20religion%20of%20Dalit%20communities%20from%20the%20583%20clans%20of%20the%20Awadh%20region.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22htt